  "prompt": "If you are deployed on a US submarine and a close relative dies, do they surface and allow you to go home for the funeral?",
  "response": "In the event of a close relative's death while a service member is deployed on a U.S. submarine, the Navy has procedures in place to address such circumstances. Generally, the submarine would make every effort to communicate the news to the service member, and if the situation is deemed urgent, they may return to port to allow the service member to go home for the funeral. \n\nHowever, the decision depends on several factors, including the specific circumstances of the situation, operational commitments, and policies in place at the time. The Navy aims to support its personnel during family emergencies, and they typically allow for bereavement leave when necessary. It\u2019s always best for service members to familiarize themselves with their command\u2019s policies regarding such situations.",
